---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Work With Me · Ray Weiss"
  description="Select commissions from Ray Weiss: custom AI voice models, AI workflow builds, and game-design consultation. I direct, and the tools implement."
>
  <div
    slot="sheet-id"
    class="sheet-id"
    aria-label="Sheet identification"
  >
    <div class="plate">
      <span class="num">PL. I.B</span> Commissions · Open to Select Work
    </div>
    <div class="edition">Edition 2026.06 · Brooklyn, NY</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <header class="hero">
      <img
        src="/counter-rw.svg"
        alt="Ray Weiss unit counter"
        class="counter"
        width="96"
        height="72"
      />
      <div>
        <h1>Work With Me</h1>
        <p class="dek">A small number of commissions a year.</p>
        <div class="slug" aria-label="Identification">
          <span><strong>UNIT</strong> RW / 26</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>TYPE</strong> Designer-Director</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>STATUS</strong> Open, selective</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>SCALE</strong> Solo + tools</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="bio">
      <p>
        Same method as everything else on this site: I direct, and the tools implement. I take on a
        small number of projects a year, in the three places where this division of labor holds. The
        design judgment is mine. The implementation is fast and cheap because the tools got good.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section aria-labelledby="commissions">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="commissions">
          <span class="pl">PL. I.B</span>Commissions
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">04 services ——</span>
      </div>
      <ol class="infra-list">
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Delivery</span><span class="v">2 to 3 weeks</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Runs</span><span class="v">Locally</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Weights</span><span class="v">Yours</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="https://lerugray.github.io/the-elect/" class="infra-title">
            Custom voice &amp; persona models &rarr;
          </a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            A small open model fine-tuned to one register: a historical figure, a brand, a house
            style, your own notes. The Elect is the public demonstration, trained on public-domain
            text with clear provenance. You bring the corpus. I direct the training, and I decide
            what stays in and what gets cut. The output carries your register, not the model's
            defaults.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Setup</span><span class="v">$1,200 fixed</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Retainer</span><span class="v">$750 / mo</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Advisory</span><span class="v">$100 / hr</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Turnaround</span><span class="v">7 to 14 days</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/generalstaff" class="infra-title">AI workflow &amp; automation builds</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            Automation for the unglamorous parts of a workflow: email triage, intake routing,
            template-driven document generation, scheduled follow-ups. I build the system, write the
            documentation, and run a handover until your team operates it alone. I operate AI agents.
            I do not write traditional code. The architecture is GeneralStaff, the framework I run my
            own work on: thirty-plus projects under a reviewer gate that rejects about one change in
            ten before it ships.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Price</span><span class="v">$400 to $800</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Terms</span><span class="v">Half up front</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Runs</span><span class="v">In your browser</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/wargame-modules" class="infra-title">Digital wargame modules &rarr;</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            The wargame you own, playable in a browser. Rules enforced by an engine, bookkeeping
            and chart lookups automated, hotseat play with hidden information masked. Four modules
            built over five weeks for one returning client. Monster games quoted per project.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span><span class="k">Scope</span><span class="v">Per project</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Domain</span><span class="v">Tabletop + digital</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/conflict-simulations-llc" class="infra-title">Game-design consultation</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            System design, rules audits, development, editorial passes. Tabletop and digital.
            Conflict Simulations is more than two dozen published wargames since 2017, three Charles
            S. Roberts nominations, and a release through Multi-Man Publishing. One of my AI tools
            found structural gaps in an already-published rulebook that human playtesting had missed.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="hex-rule" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="/hex-ornament.svg" alt="" width="96" height="32" />
    </div>

    <aside class="featured" aria-labelledby="start">
      <span class="section-label" id="start">Start</span>
      <h3>One email starts it</h3>
      <p class="desc">
        Email <a href="mailto:lerugray@gmail.com">lerugray@gmail.com</a>. State what you are building
        and the one problem you need solved. If the work fits, I reply with scope and price. If it
        does not, I say so.
      </p>
      <a href="mailto:lerugray@gmail.com" class="cta">Email me &rarr;</a>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
